## 🔩 HE600 Device Parts & Components

The HE600 medical device is composed of multiple hardware and software components working together to ensure accurate data collection, processing, and monitoring. 

---

### 🧠 1. Embedded Controller (Microcontroller Unit - MCU)
- Core processing unit of the device
- Handles sensor data acquisition and processing
- Executes firmware logic and communication protocols
- Ensures real-time responsiveness

---

### 🌡️ 2. Sensor Modules
These are responsible for collecting patient health data.

#### Types of Sensors:
- Temperature Sensor → Measures body temperature
- Pressure Sensor → Measures physical pressure or force
- Motion Sensor → Detects movement/activity
- (Optional) Pulse/Oxygen Sensor → Monitors vital signs

---

### 🔋 3. Power Supply Unit
- Provides power to the device
- Includes:
  - Battery (rechargeable/non-rechargeable)
  - Voltage regulation module
- Ensures stable and uninterrupted operation

---

### 📡 4. Communication Module
- Enables data transmission to external systems
- Supported technologies:
  - Wi-Fi
  - Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE)
  - Cellular (optional)

---

### 💾 5. Storage Module
- Temporary or permanent data storage
- Stores:
  - Sensor readings
  - Logs and error data
- Used in case of network unavailability

---

### 🖥️ 6. User Interface (UI) Components
- LED Indicators → Status display (Power, Error, Active)
- Display Screen (optional) → Shows real-time data
- Buttons/Switches → User interaction

---

### 🔊 7. Alert & Notification System
- Buzzer or vibration motor
- Triggers alerts in case of abnormal readings
- Supports real-time patient safety

---

### 🔐 8. Security Module
- Ensures secure data transmission
- Includes:
  - Data encryption
  - Authentication mechanisms
- Helps in compliance with healthcare regulations

---

### ☁️ 9. Cloud Integration Layer
- Receives data from device
- Provides:
  - Data storage
  - API access
  - Integration with dashboards

---

### 📊 10. Monitoring Dashboard
- Used by healthcare professionals
- Features:
  - Real-time data visualization
  - Alerts and notifications
  - Historical data analysis

---

## 🔄 Component Interaction Flow

1. Sensors collect patient data  
2. MCU processes and validates data  
3. Data is stored locally (if needed)  
4. Communication module sends data to cloud  
5. Cloud services process and store data  
6. Dashboard displays data to users  
7. Alerts triggered if abnormal values detected  

---

## ⚠️ Reliability Considerations

- Redundant data validation
- Fault-tolerant communication
- Low power consumption design
- High accuracy sensors
- Secure data handling
